00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:50.610
The way they play has a kind of
intensity and commitment to it

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:52.480
that is not to be beat; right?

00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:54.960
Any of us who are musicians can
respect that when we see it.

00:07:54.960 --> 00:07:57.090
And we generally know
it when we see it.

00:07:57.090 --> 00:07:59.500
And these guys, and there
are a few women in the group.

00:07:59.500 --> 00:08:00.800
But they're mostly guys.

00:08:00.800 --> 00:08:04.820
These guys play taiko, you know,
like it's an extreme sport.

00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:07.130
And, in fact, there
are very closely,

00:08:07.130 --> 00:08:10.290
a closely related taiko group
in Japan that is in fact known

00:08:10.290 --> 00:08:13.580
for running a marathon,
and I mean like a marathon,

00:08:13.580 --> 00:08:16.400
26-point whatever mile marathon.

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.980
And then playing a taiko
concert at the finish line.

00:08:18.980 --> 00:08:20.280
You know, this kind of thing.

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:23.140
So that does go on
in the taiko world.

00:08:23.140 --> 00:08:27.050
I would, I hasten to say that
it's a minority of groups

00:08:27.050 --> 00:08:28.350
that do that kind of thing.

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:31.770
But Kodo and Ondekoza,
the related group,

00:08:31.770 --> 00:08:34.240
do do that kind of thing.

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:38.170
That's not what I'm going
to be talking about today.

00:08:38.170 --> 00:08:39.550
Even though all taiko
players know

00:08:39.550 --> 00:08:40.960
about these groups from Japan.

00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:42.260
And what they're like.

00:08:42.260 --> 00:08:43.570
And how they think and all that.

00:08:43.570 --> 00:08:45.770
But taiko is, as I always say,

00:08:45.770 --> 00:08:48.660
it's both a very
old form of music.

00:08:48.660 --> 00:08:52.020
And a very new and contemporary
one all at the same time.

00:08:52.020 --> 00:08:53.620
And it has deep roots

00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:58.690
in two Japanese religions,
Buddhism and Shinto.

00:08:58.690 --> 00:09:01.120
There's much more to be
said about all these points.

00:09:01.120 --> 00:09:03.560
But in coming to North America,

00:09:03.560 --> 00:09:07.370
and by that I mean the
United States and Canada.

00:09:07.370 --> 00:09:10.290
Taiko has assumed
very different kinds

00:09:10.290 --> 00:09:12.630
of meanings than
it has in Japan.

00:09:12.630 --> 00:09:15.070
It is still closely related
to what goes on in Japan

00:09:15.070 --> 00:09:17.890
because taiko is huge in Japan.

00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:22.460
Nonetheless, the meanings and
the kinds of cultural things

00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:24.970
that taiko does for
Japanese-American

00:09:24.970 --> 00:09:27.670
and Asian-American communities
is profoundly different

00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:30.660
than what it does for
Japanese communities in Japan.

00:09:30.660 --> 00:09:31.960
All right.

00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:34.800
What it does in the U.S. is
it serves the kinds of needs

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:37.640
that Asian-Americans communities
have in terms of struggling

00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:40.110
for equality, for
access to resources.

00:09:40.110 --> 00:09:41.580
For public recognition.

00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:44.350
For the right to
speak and to be heard.

00:09:44.350 --> 00:09:46.640
And so on and so forth.

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:49.040
Taiko has come to
be, my argument is,

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:51.720
that taiko is central to
those kinds of struggles

00:09:51.720 --> 00:09:54.050
for Asian-Americans
at this point.

00:09:54.050 --> 00:09:55.520
And I'm talking about
things like this.

00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:57.620
I'm not going to go
into it in great detail.

00:09:57.620 --> 00:09:59.540
But in case I need
to convince anyone

00:09:59.540 --> 00:10:01.430
that Asian-Americans
have struggles.

00:10:01.430 --> 00:10:02.870
These are two examples.

00:10:02.870 --> 00:10:04.310
You know, the Chinese
Exclusion Act.

00:10:04.310 --> 00:10:08.060
Which took a long
time to discontinue.

00:10:08.060 --> 00:10:12.450
To close. To, you
know, to, anyway.

00:10:12.450 --> 00:10:15.580
And then the Japanese-American
internment, of course.

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:17.490
And that has just
been in the news again

00:10:17.490 --> 00:10:21.980
with the supposed overturning
the Korematsu decision; right?

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:23.960
But in a way that
really troubles a lot

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:25.810
of Japanese-Americans
as a matter of fact.

00:10:25.810 --> 00:10:27.990
So these are the
kinds of things.

00:10:27.990 --> 00:10:29.290
And there are many other issues

00:10:29.290 --> 00:10:31.620
that Asian-American
communities struggle with.

00:10:31.620 --> 00:10:32.920
Have struggled with.

00:10:32.920 --> 00:10:36.210
Continue to have
to struggle with.

00:10:36.210 --> 00:10:37.560
Taiko is part of all of that.

00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:40.330
And I'm going to try
and show you some ways

00:10:40.330 --> 00:10:41.730
in which it is as I proceed.

00:10:41.730 --> 00:10:44.580
Because not even all taiko
players want to think

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:47.670
of what they do as being
embedded, you know,

00:10:47.670 --> 00:10:50.250
in these long-term
struggles for place.

00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:51.590
For presence.

00:10:51.590 --> 00:10:54.890
A short story on sort of
the demographics of taiko

00:10:54.890 --> 00:10:56.330
in the U.S. and Canada.

00:10:56.330 --> 00:10:57.940
Goes something like this.

00:10:57.940 --> 00:10:59.240
In terms of gender, it's

00:10:59.240 --> 00:11:02.690
about 60 percent women
and 40 percent men.

00:11:02.690 --> 00:11:05.910
For a long time actually the
percentage of women was higher.

00:11:05.910 --> 00:11:08.130
Maybe like 75 percent
for a long time.

00:11:08.130 --> 00:11:09.750
And they seem to
be shifting a bit.

00:11:09.750 --> 00:11:15.320
And I'm basing these numbers on
a census that was done in 2016.

00:11:15.320 --> 00:11:17.570
So the numbers are
pretty current.

00:11:17.570 --> 00:11:18.880
About 60 percent

00:11:18.880 --> 00:11:21.840
of all performers
are Asian-American

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:23.300
or Asian-Canadian.

00:11:23.300 --> 00:11:26.370
The others are primarily white.

00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:27.800
And the numbers of Latinx

00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:31.720
or African-American taiko
players are really small.

00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:34.540
And I don't think that's a
coincidence or arbitrary.

00:11:34.540 --> 00:11:36.480
I think that taiko
is serving the needs

00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:39.460
of two ethnic groups as it were.

00:11:39.460 --> 00:11:41.180
Racial and ethnic groups.

00:11:41.180 --> 00:11:45.500
And a majority of taiko players
are on the young side of things.

00:11:45.500 --> 00:11:48.580
In their 20s and 30s primarily.

00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:51.340
Most of us play as
a leisure activity.

00:11:51.340 --> 00:11:54.610
There are very, very few,
like, professional, full-time,

00:11:54.610 --> 00:11:56.390
you know,
make-a-living-through-taiko kind

00:11:56.390 --> 00:11:59.360
of people who are part
of the taiko community.

00:11:59.360 --> 00:12:01.860
Most of us are in
community-based groups.

00:12:01.860 --> 00:12:04.540
Some are on university campuses.

00:12:04.540 --> 00:12:08.390
But most, the vast majority
of us are in community groups.

00:12:08.390 --> 00:12:09.690
And you know what?

00:12:09.690 --> 00:12:12.300
The vast, vast majority
of us are in California.

00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:16.200
Both Southern California and
Northern California, yeah.

00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:17.960
Now, all of this is changing

00:12:17.960 --> 00:12:20.590
by the minute, you
know, by the day.

00:12:20.590 --> 00:12:25.190
Taiko is in a period of
rapid expansion right now.

00:12:25.190 --> 00:12:27.640
In fact, it's expanding
exponentially.

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:30.270
There are more and more taiko
groups every time I turn around;

00:12:30.270 --> 00:12:31.570
right?

00:12:31.570 --> 00:12:33.230
So these numbers are
going to change again.

00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:36.430
And I wonder if at some point
California will not be the

00:12:36.430 --> 00:12:39.780
center of the, you know, North
American taiko universe; right?

00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:41.080
You know, I don't know.

00:12:41.080 --> 00:12:42.720
Check back in five
years, ten years.

00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:44.020
It's going to change.

00:12:44.020 --> 00:12:45.320
I don't know how though.

