00:43:58.350 --> 00:43:59.650
But the Fandango scene,

00:43:59.650 --> 00:44:03.750
son jarocho is very
lively right now.

00:44:03.750 --> 00:44:05.050
And you can see how
people just sort

00:44:05.050 --> 00:44:06.610
of gather into a loose circle.

00:44:06.610 --> 00:44:08.760
And there's dancing
going on in the middle.

00:44:08.760 --> 00:44:14.250
And jaranas playing all around
the outside of the circle.

00:44:14.250 --> 00:44:20.100
Fandango. Yeah, this is Cesar
Castro, who does live this LA.

00:44:21.150 --> 00:44:22.450
So too much text.

00:44:22.450 --> 00:44:24.780
But the point being that
there's a lot of similarities

00:44:24.780 --> 00:44:26.500
between these two forms.

00:44:26.500 --> 00:44:29.630
Both are all about
participation.

00:44:29.630 --> 00:44:32.190
They're not about
professional trained people.

00:44:32.190 --> 00:44:35.730
Both of them are open-ended and
can go on for quite a while.

00:44:35.730 --> 00:44:38.990
It's not like, you know, they do
say like, we're going to start

00:44:38.990 --> 00:44:41.130
at 7:00 and end around
9:00 kind of thing.

00:44:41.130 --> 00:44:43.710
But they could go on as long
as you want them to go on.

00:44:43.710 --> 00:44:46.230
They are noncompetitive
in their spirit.

00:44:46.230 --> 00:44:48.030
Doesn't matter whether
you're a good dancer

00:44:48.030 --> 00:44:49.630
or a completely clueless dancer.

00:44:49.630 --> 00:44:51.440
You just get out
there, and you do it.

00:44:51.440 --> 00:44:52.740
And nobody cares.

00:44:52.740 --> 00:44:54.960
Everybody admires good
dancing when they see it.

00:44:54.960 --> 00:44:57.270
But you don't have to
be good to be part.

00:44:57.270 --> 00:44:59.860
Both of them are
transnational in the ways

00:44:59.860 --> 00:45:02.290
that performers are
connected to people

00:45:02.290 --> 00:45:03.830
in the countries of origin.

00:45:03.830 --> 00:45:06.760
And there's often
movement, continuous,

00:45:06.760 --> 00:45:08.060
between the two places.

00:45:08.060 --> 00:45:09.920
The two homelands.

00:45:09.920 --> 00:45:11.220
One emerged at part

00:45:11.220 --> 00:45:13.460
of the Chicanx movement
in the United States.

00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:14.760
Fandango is very old.

00:45:14.760 --> 00:45:17.560
But in the United States it was
part of the Chicano movement.

00:45:17.560 --> 00:45:20.660
Obon's a little different
in that it's been part

00:45:20.660 --> 00:45:23.670
of JA community for over
a century at this point.

00:45:23.670 --> 00:45:27.490
And was revived after
World War Two.

00:45:27.490 --> 00:45:30.950
And you need to see FandangObon
before I tell you more about it.

00:45:30.950 --> 00:45:34.650
It was on the mall two years
